api_list.description: The Countries endpoint gives you Country data like its Name, Flag, IsoCode, Continent and other related Country data.                         The Countries endpoint also gives the chance to order Leagues under the same Country. On the off chance that for instance, you need to demonstrate the Leagues per Country on your site/application, this may be a valuable endpoint for you by use the Leagues Endpoint.

api_list.name: Country by ID
All Leagues
api_list.description: The Leagues endpoint would return a response with all Leagues available in your plan you are subscribed. The Leagues endpoint give you League data for example ID, Name, Country, Coverage etc. The Leagues endpoint also is used in combination with the Season or Seasons Endpoints. The Seasons Endpoint show information about all seasons available for the specific Leagues.

api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://soccersapi.p.rapidapi.com/leagues"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "soccersapi.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
